    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    <strong>Ice Fishing Tips</strong>
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        Always check ice thickness (at least 4 inches safe for foot travel)
    </li>
    <li>
        Use insulated boots and layered clothing
    </li>
    <li>
        Bring safety gear: rope, spikes, ice auger
    </li>
</ul>
<h2 class="text-3xl text-teal-900 font-bold my-4">
    <strong>Sustainable and Ethical Fishing Practices</strong>
</h2>
<p class="mb-4">
    Oregonians take pride in preserving nature. Here's how to fish responsibly:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Catch and release properly</strong>: Wet hands before handling fish.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Pack out all trash</strong>: Leave your spot cleaner than you found it.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Avoid sensitive habitats</strong>: Don’t trample spawning grounds or stream beds.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Support hatchery programs</strong>: They help sustain fish populations.
    </li>
</ul>
