    </li>
</ul>
<h2 class="text-3xl text-teal-900 font-bold my-4">
    <strong>FAQs About Fishing Near Portland, Oregon</strong>
</h2>
<p class="mb-4">
    <strong>1. Do I need a license to fish in Portland?</strong><br>
    Yes, an Oregon fishing license is required for anyone 12 years or older.
</p>
<p class="mb-4">
    <strong>2. What is the best time of year to fish in Portland?</strong><br>
    Spring and fall are ideal for trout and salmon, while summer is best for bass and panfish.
</p>
<p class="mb-4">
    <strong>3. Can I fish in downtown Portland?</strong><br>
    Yes! The Willamette River offers great spots near the Hawthorne and Steel Bridges.
</p>
<p class="mb-4">
    <strong>4. Are there any free fishing days in Oregon?</strong><br>
    Yes, ODFW hosts Free Fishing Weekends twice a year where no license is required.
</p>
<p class="mb-4">
    <strong>5. What’s the best river for steelhead near Portland?</strong><br>
    The Sandy River is highly recommended, especially from December through March.
</p>
<p class="mb-4">
    <strong>6. Where can I rent fishing gear in Portland?</strong><br>
    Try Next Adventure or Royal Treatment Fly Fishing—they offer rentals and guided trips.
</p>
